cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about discovering subword and word units from raw speech, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the challenge involves processing raw speech signals. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the challenge aims at constructing systems that generalize across languages and adapt to new speakers, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the challenge involves developing intelligent systems that can learn from raw speech data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as many of the models used in the challenge are based on neural networks.
